data.description: Introducing a charming home nestled in a peaceful cul-de-sac, featuring a half acre lot that offers privacy and tranquility. No HOA.  The fenced-in flat back yard includes a delightful tree house for outdoor adventures.   Granite stone and lightly shaded gray cabinets add a touch of elegance to the kitchen space.  Open dining room enjoyment with patio  access.  Adding a sophisticated touch, you'll find some updated wood floors and crown molding throughout.  The three bedrooms and two baths provide ample space for families or guests. The bathrooms have undergone renovations, adding a modern and stylish touch.  One of the highlights of this property is the cozy fireplace in the living room, creating a warm and inviting atmosphere.  Convenience is key with this location, as it is just a 15-minute drive to uptown and to University area. Additionally, you'll discover Delta Creek Neighborhood Park located on Linda Lake Drive.  Roof and AC replaced.
